{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"B\n    \n      Incremental Migration (Recommended)\n      Migrate in 4 ordered steps, each independently deployable and testable:\n      \n        Step 1: Add Turborepo + shared packages (ui, types, config). Existing apps/web keeps working.\n        Step 2: Create apps/marketing (Next.js) — extract public/SEO pages from apps/web.\n        Step 3: Create apps/platform (Vite + TanStack) — migrate authenticated pages.\n        Step 4: Dockerize everything + K8s manifests + CI/CD for OVH.\n      \n      \n        \n          Pros\n          \n            Each step is small, testable, and reversible\n            Working software at every stage\n            Can ship Step 1-2 while Step 3-4 are in progress\n          \n        \n        \n          Cons\n          \n            Transitional period where old and new coexist\n            Slightly more total git history","choice":"b","id":null,"timestamp":1775329327116}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A\n    \n      Big Bang Migration\n      Restructure the entire repo in one go: add Turborepo, split frontend into marketing + platform apps, set up K8s manifests, CI/CD — then deploy everything together.\n      \n        \n          Pros\n          \n            Clean break — no transitional state\n            Everything works together from day one\n            One PR to review\n          \n        \n        \n          Cons\n          \n            Large risky change — hard to debug if something breaks\n            Weeks before anything is deployable\n            Existing working code gets disrupted","choice":"a","id":null,"timestamp":1775329336454}
